Diarrhea was the most common disease problem observed over the entire course this study beginning on D2 (Fig. 2
). Other disease problems observed during the study were navel inflammation (by palpation) and respiratory disease (scored as described in the methods). The frequency of diarrhea in both groups was high on D7 (COL + calves 55.5%; COL − calves 70.0%), and D14 (COL + calves 77.8%; COL − calves 60.0%). Later observations yielded a decrease in diarrhea frequency on D21 (COL + calves 55.5%; COL − calves 50.0%), and D28 (COL + calves 44.4%; COL − calves 50.0%). The frequency of diarrhea diagnosis (fecal score 2 and 3) was similar between groups for all points of measurement (P
 ≥ 0.05).
